message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Montenegro in the past 100 years is its declaration of independence from Serbia in 2006. This event marked the end of the State Union of Serbia and Montenegro, which was the successor to the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. Montenegrin citizens voted in a referendum for the country to become an independent nation, leading to its recognition as a sovereign state by the international community. This event shaped the modern-day political and national identity of Montenegro.
